# Chapter 11 — Modules

A module is a named bundle of `define`s. `import` pulls names into scope. `verb layers` are the runtime's way of loading whole vocabularies at once.

## Declare

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(module geom
  (export area)
  (define (area r) (* 3.14159 r r)))
</pre>

## Import

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(import geom)
(area 5)
</pre>

## Verb layers

<pre data-runnable data-lang=\"sakura-scheme\">
(import (verbs canvas))
</pre>

> **Sakura says**
>
> Verb layers are the reason I can drive a canvas, a chat, or a shop from the same REPL — each layer is one module I import when I need it. `,apropos canvas/` lists everything the canvas verb layer ships.

